<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-22T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-22T08:00:00-05:00" n="1071" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1071">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.01/36: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-22T13:00:00+00:00">April 22, 1931—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 22—11:30 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>28. Your number 12, April 21, 4 p.m. British colleague took action 12:30
                            today. Minister of Foreign Affairs will receive me at 4:30 this
                            afternoon for delivery of note authorized by you.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>